<div class="about-hero">
    <div class="about-hero-inner">
        <div class="breadcrumb"><a href="index.html">Home</a> / About</div>
        <span class="eyebrow">Our Story</span>
        <h1>Empowering Communities Through <em>Connection</em> and Care</h1>
        <div class="about-hero-sub">
            <p>MindConnect was founded in the Inland Empire with a simple but urgent belief: every person deserves access to mental health support, regardless of their income, language, or zip code.</p>
            <p>We started locally. We think nationally. And we work every day to connect people to the resources, support, and community they need to thrive.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- STORY -->
<section class="story-section">
    <div class="story-inner">
        <div class="story-layout">
            <div class="story-sidebar reveal">
                <div class="section-tag">Our Origin</div>
                <h2>Born from the Inland Empire</h2>
                <p>Founded by community members who lived through the gaps in mental health care, MindConnect is built on firsthand understanding of what underserved communities need.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="story-content reveal">
                <h3>The Problem We Couldn't Ignore</h3>
                <p>The Inland Empire — like many regions across the United States — faces a profound shortage of mental health resources. With only <strong>35 primary care providers per 100,000 residents</strong>, and more than 500,000 people in the region affected by mental health conditions, the gap between need and access is staggering.</p>
                <p>Our founders saw firsthand how families struggled: long wait times for appointments, confusing insurance requirements, language barriers, and the simple fear of not knowing where to start. Something had to change.</p>

                <div class="story-pullquote">
                    "We kept hearing the same story — 'I knew I needed help, I just didn't know how to get it.' That became our mission: be the bridge."
                </div>

                <h3>Why We Built MindConnect</h3>
                <p>MindConnect was created to solve a coordination problem. The resources often exist — the free clinics, the psychiatrists accepting new patients, the wellness programs, the pharmacies with assistance programs. What's missing is the <strong>connective tissue</strong> that helps people find and access them.</p>
                <p>We step into that role. We map the landscape of available care, build relationships with providers who share our values, and guide individuals through the process from first contact to ongoing support.</p>

                <h3>What Makes Us Different</h3>
                <p>Unlike traditional healthcare navigators, MindConnect provides <strong>ongoing peer support</strong>, not just referrals. We stay with you. We check in. We adapt to your changing needs. And we do it in both English and Spanish, because language should never be a barrier to healing.</p>
                <p>We're also building an educational infrastructure — equipping individuals, families, and caregivers with the knowledge they need to understand, manage, and improve mental health outcomes over the long term.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

